windowSelect(25.10)                                        windowSelect(25.10)

Name
       windowSelect - Selects all objects within the specified area

Syntax
       windowSelect

       [-help]

       <area>

       Selects all objects within the specified area.

       Note: This command works only in GUI mode.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each windowSelect parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man windowSelect

       <area> Specifies the coordinates of the window area to be selected. You
              can specify <area>using any of the following formats:

              *

                <x1 y1 x2 y2>Example: windowSelect 10 10 20 20

              * "<x1 y1 x2 y2">

                Example: windowSelect "10 10 20 20"

              * {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}

                Example: windowSelect {10 10 20 20}

              * [list 10 10 20 20]

                Example: windowSelect [list 10 10 20 20]

              *

                [dbGet $inst.box]

                Example: windowSelect [dbGet $inst.box]

                Where inst is a variable that has already been set.

Example
       The  following command selects objects that are totally enclosed by the
       area with coordinates defined as (x=10, y=200) and (x=100, y=50):

       windowSelect 10 200 100 50

